WEBVTT

00:04.226 --> 00:07.411
Where do you go for stability when life feels unsteady?

00:07.992 --> 00:16.867
In Peter's first letter to early Christians, he likens Jesus Christ to a cornerstone in ancient architecture, the foundation on which everything else must rest.

00:17.448 --> 00:30.130
In today's sermon, Tim Keller looks at Peter's cornerstone metaphor and shows us how putting our full trust in Jesus and his ultimate act of salvation lays the foundation strong enough to sustain us no matter what comes our way.

00:37.858 --> 00:47.450
We've been going through the book of 1 Peter, and we get to a new section, and I'm going to just read chapter 2, 1 Peter, verses 4 to 8.

00:47.670 --> 00:49.052
That's all we have time to look at.

00:49.753 --> 00:52.597
And just really get an introduction to this marvelous passage.

00:53.798 --> 01:00.386
But let me just read chapter 2, verse 4 to 8, and get us ready to meet God over His table in the Lord's Supper.

01:03.170 --> 01:06.514
As you come to Him, the living stone

01:06.850 --> 01:10.474
Rejected by men but chosen by God and precious to Him.

01:11.295 --> 01:20.985
You also, like living stones, are being built into a spiritual house to be a holy priesthood, offering spiritual sacrifices acceptable to God through Jesus Christ.

01:21.686 --> 01:30.215
For in Scripture it says, see, I lay a stone in Zion, a chosen and precious cornerstone, and the one who trusts in Him will never be put to shame.

01:30.255 --> 01:33.298
Now to you who believe this stone is precious.

01:33.858 --> 01:38.024
But to those who do not believe, the stone the builders rejected has become the capstone.

01:38.685 --> 01:42.009
And a stone that causes men to stumble in a rock that makes them fall.

01:42.470 --> 01:46.615
They stumble because they disobey the message, which is also what they were destined for.

01:47.256 --> 01:48.778
And let's stop right there.

01:49.319 --> 01:51.462
This is this marvelous passage.

01:52.203 --> 02:03.538
Come to him to that living stone, rejected by men but chosen by God and precious to him, for it is written, I lay a stone in Zion.

02:03.714 --> 02:09.581
a chosen and precious cornerstone, and the one who trusts in him will never be put to shame."

02:11.083 --> 02:16.991
It's just a tremendous statement, and the background of it is ancient architecture.

02:18.272 --> 02:20.975
There are several characteristics of a cornerstone.

02:22.477 --> 02:25.061
The cornerstone was the first stone laid.

02:25.101 --> 02:29.426
It was the first stone laid because

02:29.794 --> 02:36.123
All of the dimensions of the rest of the house were projected off of the dimensions of the cornerstone.

02:36.804 --> 02:41.550
The cornerstone was the first stone late, and it had to be the most perfectly cut stone.

02:42.551 --> 02:45.676
Because you see what the cornerstone would be, would be what the house would be.

02:45.756 --> 02:48.940
The lines of the cornerstone become the lines of the house.

02:49.381 --> 02:59.314
If the cornerstone is not cut at perfectly right angles, for example, to the ground, then the house will not be at good right angles.

02:59.426 --> 03:01.810
Whatever the cornerstone is, the house is.

03:02.631 --> 03:08.139
If you go to the flat iron building and you look at the cornerstone of the flat iron building, it's a flat iron.

03:08.780 --> 03:15.310
If the cornerstone is rectangle, the lines go out from the cornerstone and the house is a rectangle.

03:15.570 --> 03:18.835
If the cornerstone is a flat iron, the house is a flat iron shape.

03:19.195 --> 03:22.841
If the corner stone is off, the house is off.

03:24.002 --> 03:26.386
If the corner stone is true, the house is true.

03:26.978 --> 03:31.043
And therefore the cornerstone was the most perfectly cut and shaped stone.

03:31.884 --> 03:34.407
Thirdly, it was the first stone, it was the most perfect stone.

03:34.788 --> 03:49.906
Thirdly, it had to be the toughest and strongest stone because if there was any lack of integrity in the stone, if there were any structural flaws or fissures, if it crumbled in any way, the house, the entire house would be compromised or even lost.

03:50.786 --> 03:54.932
It was the one stone on which everything else was really resting in many ways.

03:54.972 --> 03:59.538
And so if it crumbled, more than any other one particular stone, the house would crumble.

04:00.139 --> 04:03.924
And therefore, since it was the first stone, it was the most perfect stone.

04:04.325 --> 04:06.328
It had to be the stone of the most tough material.

04:06.768 --> 04:08.851
It was usually the largest stone for all the above.

04:09.131 --> 04:13.758
Therefore, literally, the cornerstone was the most precious stone.

04:14.779 --> 04:17.343
It was most precious because literally it was the most expensive.

04:18.024 --> 04:19.666
It was the most labor-intensive.

04:19.938 --> 04:31.432
It was not unusual for a builder to spend as much time finding the cornerstone, quarrying the right kind of stone, finding the cornerstone and cutting the cornerstone perfectly.

04:31.452 --> 04:39.762
As much time on that as the whole rest of the building, it was literally far and away the most expensive part of the ancient building.

04:40.323 --> 04:49.234
Now, all of this is brought to the fore, all this is the background,

04:49.698 --> 05:03.564
Peter says, come to him to that living capstone, which is the cornerstone, rejected by men but chosen by God, for it is written, whoever trusts in him will never be put to shame.

05:04.525 --> 05:12.180
Now, what is this teach us about Jesus, especially tonight as we're getting ready to seek to meet him at his table through the bread and the cup?

05:12.520 --> 05:13.522
And the answer is,

05:13.858 --> 05:17.102
This tells us that Jesus is to be your life's foundation.

05:17.122 --> 05:19.865
This also tells us that Jesus is our federal head.

05:19.925 --> 05:24.550
And thirdly, it tells us that Jesus is to be the love of our life.

05:25.991 --> 05:26.832
He's the foundation.

05:26.892 --> 05:28.654
He's our federal head.

05:29.215 --> 05:30.156
He's the love of our life.

05:30.596 --> 05:32.478
It's all in the cornerstone metaphor here.

05:32.498 --> 05:35.061
Look, number one, he's the life foundation.

05:35.161 --> 05:38.265
Notice it says, the one who trusts in him.

05:38.305 --> 05:40.267
Now, what does it mean to trust?

05:41.729 --> 05:43.090
To come to him,

05:44.418 --> 05:54.255
who is the cornerstone, all the other stones came to the cornerstone, and all the other stones were set in place along the lines of the cornerstone.

05:54.736 --> 06:02.450
And therefore, when the Bible talks about believing in Jesus Christ, it's talking about something far more than just ascent.

06:02.850 --> 06:13.608
He's talking about far more than just sort of picking up his teachings and saying, I believe in his teachings, or I believe in his ethics, or I believe that he died on the cross for sins and so on.

06:13.668 --> 06:14.911
It means much more than that.

06:16.153 --> 06:23.986
It means shifting the center of your gravity to him.

06:24.066 --> 06:25.568
There's an exercise, which I hate.

06:25.728 --> 06:32.656
I don't know if you like it, but there are some sometimes in group building retreats.

06:33.137 --> 06:40.465
Somebody dreamed this terrible thing up, this form of torture years ago, to try to get groups to trust each other.

06:40.746 --> 06:41.306
Have you ever done it?

06:41.707 --> 06:45.732
You're supposed to stand in the middle of a circle, and everybody stands around you.

06:45.752 --> 06:49.216
You're supposed to close your eyes and keep your body stiff and let yourself fall.

06:49.997 --> 06:51.218
Have you seen that?

06:51.362 --> 06:52.984
This is supposed to build up trust.

06:53.004 --> 06:54.065
Now, let's not get into that.

06:54.726 --> 06:56.849
But let me just tell you what's interesting about it.

06:58.831 --> 07:01.014
What you've got to do is you've got to shift the center of gravity.

07:01.194 --> 07:07.822
If you let yourself lean far enough over so that the center of gravity of your body is out from your own foundation, your own feet.

07:08.363 --> 07:11.146
If it's out far enough away, you have to fall.

07:11.547 --> 07:20.658
You shift your center of gravity to somebody else's, somebody standing around you in this little tight circle, and that person has to hold you up, has to catch you.

07:20.802 --> 07:24.005
If you shift your center of gravity, that person, you are vulnerable.

07:25.367 --> 07:32.094
That person now, his or her feet, his or her foundation has to become your foundation, or wham.

07:32.134 --> 07:37.259
You know what it means when it says, those who trust in him will never be able to shame?

07:37.920 --> 07:40.923
To trust in Jesus Christ is to make him the cornerstone of your life.

07:41.003 --> 07:42.624
It's to shift the center of your gravity.

07:43.666 --> 07:48.050
Your cornerstone, see, whenever somebody says,

07:48.706 --> 07:49.787
I believe in Jesus.

07:49.968 --> 07:50.608
I'm a Christian.

07:51.209 --> 07:53.492
You also have to ask yourself, fine, great.

07:54.093 --> 07:56.255
But what is my functional cornerstone?

07:57.677 --> 07:59.419
What is the center of my gravity?

08:02.503 --> 08:05.346
The cornerstone is the thing that sets the course for the building.

08:06.347 --> 08:09.311
And your cornerstone sets the course of your life as a whole.

08:09.351 --> 08:12.635
I've seen this happen many, many times.

08:13.356 --> 08:15.218
Some people who are so frantic

08:15.490 --> 08:16.371
Why are they frantic?

08:16.852 --> 08:19.256
Because what is their functional cornerstone?

08:19.276 --> 08:22.081
Maybe it's success, maybe it's a claim, maybe it's possessions.

08:23.343 --> 08:29.233
And your real cornerstone, the thing that you really base your life on, will always set the course of your life.

08:30.255 --> 08:32.679
It will project the lines out into the rest of your life.

08:33.280 --> 08:34.222
And you'll be frantic.

08:35.183 --> 08:37.007
There's other people who are really very, very different.

08:37.087 --> 08:41.394
Other people, essentially your cornerstone is stasis.

08:41.986 --> 08:47.212
People in big cities, your cornerstone is turmoil and getting ahead.

08:47.632 --> 08:53.899
But people in small towns, their cornerstone is stasis, which means keeping things the way they are.

08:53.939 --> 08:55.000
Tradition.

08:55.982 --> 09:00.507
Letting the normal family system, even a sick family system, stay in place.

09:00.867 --> 09:01.728
That's your cornerstone.

09:01.748 --> 09:02.989
That's what makes you feel secure.

09:03.690 --> 09:06.293
To become a Christian doesn't mean you just change your mind.

09:06.734 --> 09:09.517
It doesn't mean you just believe in a new set of doctrines.

09:09.557 --> 09:10.738
It's tearing up.

09:12.930 --> 09:14.993
It's taking all the stones of your life.

09:16.795 --> 09:23.144
And instead of having them all, you know, see, shooting off of the old cornerstone, you shoot them off of the new cornerstone, Jesus.

09:24.085 --> 09:27.049
You come to Him to the living stone.

09:27.109 --> 09:35.680
I've so often seen very frantic people when they really start to make Jesus their cornerstone start to mellow out.

09:36.101 --> 09:39.986
And I've seen very, very lethargic people

09:40.418 --> 09:43.522
when they come to make Jesus their cornerstone, start to speed up.

09:44.983 --> 09:49.428
Because you see, Jesus is to trust in him means you build off of him.

09:50.089 --> 09:51.270
He becomes your cornerstone.

09:51.931 --> 09:55.275
I preached a sermon on this text 14 years ago.

09:55.335 --> 09:57.217
I found the old sermon, 14 years ago.

09:57.898 --> 10:01.442
And evidently at the time, I had only two children, not three.

10:01.482 --> 10:04.205
And one of the children was a two and a half.

10:04.225 --> 10:05.967
The other child was about six months old.

10:06.528 --> 10:08.370
And I wrote this down as an illustration.

10:09.090 --> 10:15.960
I said, you know, I noticed that when my kids are sick, Kathy is very shaken, feeling that she's failing, feeling life is out of control, meaningless.

10:17.001 --> 10:22.770
And when the church is sick, Tim feels that he is very shaken, feeling like he's failing, feeling life is out of control and meaningless.

10:23.611 --> 10:28.298
It's not hard, I wrote down, to find out what our functional cornerstones really are.

10:29.319 --> 10:31.282
Your cornerstones, that's the course

10:31.554 --> 10:35.278
of the building and if the cornerstone is crumbling, the building crumbles.

10:35.659 --> 10:38.142
How do you know what the functional cornerstone of your life is?

10:38.182 --> 10:38.863
It's very simple.

10:39.403 --> 10:50.977
When the winds come and when the storm howls and when the waves come and beat against the cornerstone, the cornerstone is the one part of your life.

10:51.337 --> 10:55.282
If that shakes, if that crumbles, everything crumbles.

10:55.714 --> 10:56.597
Just look at yourself.

10:57.561 --> 10:59.207
What are the non-negotiables in your life?

10:59.548 --> 11:00.512
They're your cornerstones.

11:00.813 --> 11:03.804
What are the things that say, if I lose that, I lose everything.

11:04.205 --> 11:05.490
Those are the cornerstones.

11:06.146 --> 11:08.470
I mean, the Bible talks about this.

11:09.431 --> 11:13.858
Luke chapter 6, why do you call me Lord, Lord, says Jesus and do not the things that I say?

11:13.878 --> 11:17.544
If you do my words, you're like a man building a house upon the rock.

11:17.624 --> 11:21.249
The flood came and the winds blew and it could not be shaken.

11:21.570 --> 11:25.776
But a man who says Lord, Lord, but does not do the things that I say, does not build on me.

11:26.397 --> 11:29.362
He's like a man who builds his house on the sand.

11:29.826 --> 11:35.975
The winds howl, and the floods come, and the house falls, and great is the fall of it.

11:36.035 --> 11:36.836
That's how it goes.

11:36.917 --> 11:59.410
And when the floods come, when the troubles come into your life, and you feel like you're shaken to the roots, and you feel like your life's about the fall, you're not doing the right thing if you say, if only I could get out of this storm, if only I could get out of this wind, if only I could get out of this flood, don't you see what you should be asking, why am I so vulnerable?

12:00.226 --> 12:01.728
Why is my house shaking?

12:02.289 --> 12:02.749
Why?

12:02.810 --> 12:04.872
What is my cornerstone?

12:05.293 --> 12:08.597
What am I building my life on that would make me so vulnerable?

12:08.818 --> 12:10.280
It's not the flood that's your problem.

12:10.540 --> 12:11.501
It's the cornerstone.

12:14.586 --> 12:23.698
To believe in Jesus Christ is to never be ashamed, which means, friends, if you're a Christian, what this really means, of course,

12:24.130 --> 12:26.853
is that you notice how Peter's talking to Christians here.

12:26.954 --> 12:28.696
He says, come to him to the living stone.

12:29.176 --> 12:36.566
It really means that when you become a Christian, you tear up the old cornerstones and you say, from now on, I'm living for Christ.

12:36.626 --> 12:38.508
It's not just believing in a general way.

12:38.809 --> 12:48.962
You base your whole life on him, you build everything around him, and yet you have to spend all of your life getting more and more of the stones of your house packed in against the cornerstone.

12:49.282 --> 12:52.466
The fact of the matter is we're spending all of our lives pulling

12:53.282 --> 12:57.569
the stones away from the old corner stones, and building them back on unto Jesus.

12:58.070 --> 13:00.814
We're going to spend all of our life doing that, and that's all right.

13:01.395 --> 13:03.298
That's the process of what it means to grow.

13:04.019 --> 13:08.807
And that's the reason why Peter doesn't just say this to people who don't believe.

13:08.927 --> 13:09.788
He says that to you.

13:09.808 --> 13:16.459
If you know today that you're really not a Christian, but you're really not sure what you'd have to do, here's the start.

13:17.581 --> 13:18.322
Trust in him.

13:18.382 --> 13:20.786
It means to build your life on him.

13:21.922 --> 13:24.445
But even if you're our Christian, don't you see?

13:24.925 --> 13:26.227
We are ashamed a lot.

13:26.948 --> 13:28.750
The one who trusts in Him will never be put to shame.

13:28.770 --> 13:29.811
Well, we're ashamed all the time.

13:29.831 --> 13:30.291
You know why?

13:30.311 --> 13:32.434
Because we don't build on Him completely.

13:32.474 --> 13:34.456
Don't you see if He was our only cornerstone?

13:34.496 --> 13:44.607
If all of the stones of our lives were shooting off, if all the dimensions of our lives were shooting off of Jesus, projected off of His lines, we'd never be ashamed.

13:45.388 --> 13:46.469
We'd never be let down.

13:47.150 --> 13:48.271
We'd never be disappointed.

13:48.311 --> 13:49.272
We'd never be shattered.

13:49.633 --> 13:50.834
Come to Him.

13:52.962 --> 13:56.326
Jesus was the most influential man to ever walk the earth.

13:56.927 --> 14:01.773
And his story has been told through books, movies, and articles in hundreds of different ways.

14:02.314 --> 14:03.896
Can anything more be said about him?

14:04.656 --> 14:12.306
In his book, Jesus the King, Tim Keller journeys through the gospel of Mark to reveal how the life of Jesus helps us make sense of our lives.

14:12.927 --> 14:22.098
Dr. Keller shows us how the story of Jesus is at once cosmic, historical, and personal, calling each of us to take a fresh look at our relationship with God.

14:22.274 --> 14:32.232
During the month of March, we'll send you a copy of Jesus the King as our thanks for your gift to help gospel and life share the transforming love of Christ with people all over the world.

14:32.873 --> 14:36.079
So request your copy today at gospelandlife.com.

14:36.399 --> 14:38.804
That's gospelandlife.com.

14:39.685 --> 14:42.751
Now here's Dr. Keller with the remainder of today's teaching.

14:45.917 --> 14:46.738
Now secondly,

14:47.906 --> 14:50.248
First thing we learn here is that Jesus is our life's foundation.

14:50.489 --> 14:53.452
Secondly, we learn here that Jesus is our federal head.

14:53.532 --> 14:54.753
Now, what does that mean?

14:54.813 --> 14:55.754
Well, it means this.

14:56.235 --> 15:01.861
The cornerstone is another way of getting across the fact that we are in federation with Jesus when we believe in Him.

15:02.782 --> 15:06.485
You see, if the cornerstone is true, the house is true.

15:06.826 --> 15:08.908
If the cornerstone is erect, the house is erect.

15:08.928 --> 15:11.010
If the cornerstone is erect, then the house is erect.

15:11.050 --> 15:14.674
If the cornerstone of the cornerstone is a flat iron, the house is a flat iron.

15:15.426 --> 15:25.520
How is it possible that a human being could come into the presence of God as the text says and offer acceptable sacrifices in the presence of a holy God?

15:26.161 --> 15:32.089
How can you know that you're absolutely acceptable today in the sight of God?

15:32.689 --> 15:44.946
How can you know that no matter what you do, no matter what goes on in your life, no matter whether the, if the curtain of history came down tonight and history was over and judgment day was tonight,

15:45.186 --> 15:50.553
As John Dunn says, what if tonight, what if today was the world's last night?

15:52.456 --> 15:57.383
Could you be absolutely sure that you would be found acceptable in his sight?

15:57.583 --> 16:01.048
Could you know that God would look at you and say, this is my beloved child whom I'm well pleased?

16:01.468 --> 16:02.109
Yes, you can.

16:02.590 --> 16:03.030
You know how?

16:04.172 --> 16:11.442
Because Jesus Christ, the cornerstone is precious, absolutely precious to the builder.

16:12.194 --> 16:16.863
We said, the cornerstone is the most precious, the most expensive of all the stones to the builder.

16:17.183 --> 16:18.085
The builder is God.

16:18.405 --> 16:20.089
He's building up his house, you see.

16:20.229 --> 16:21.892
We're all living stones in the house.

16:21.952 --> 16:22.794
That's the image here.

16:22.854 --> 16:24.737
We'll look at that more in the future.

16:25.158 --> 16:29.887
But Jesus Christ is infinitely precious to the builder, his father.

16:29.927 --> 16:33.874
And all of that preciousness actually passes on to the rest of us.

16:34.530 --> 16:38.775
Whatever he is, we are if we're packed in against him, if we're united to him.

16:39.836 --> 16:41.077
Let's put it a couple ways.

16:41.117 --> 16:42.398
We can put it several ways.

16:43.560 --> 16:48.925
The Bible tells us in John chapter 1 verse 18 that the son is in the bosom of the Father.

16:50.727 --> 16:53.470
From all eternity, let me read you a couple quotes.

16:54.111 --> 16:59.257
The Father and the Son before the world were made spent countless ages rejoicing in each other's presence.

16:59.937 --> 17:01.939
Think for a moment how the Father loves Jesus.

17:02.800 --> 17:04.402
We're told that they have spent

17:04.738 --> 17:11.925
All beginningless eternity, pouring love and pleasure and glory into each other's hearts in degrees of depth and power, which we cannot imagine.

17:12.387 --> 17:13.450
This is John Flovello.

17:13.571 --> 17:14.093
Oh, Puritan.

17:14.113 --> 17:14.816
He put it this way.

17:14.856 --> 17:16.562
God is the fountain.

17:16.802 --> 17:21.487
The ocean, the center of joy, and Jesus lay in the very bosom of the fountain of joy.

17:21.527 --> 17:31.677
Day in and day out, the Father immediately, fully, everlastingly, let out this overpowering bliss and rapture and ecstasy and delight into the soul of Jesus.

17:32.217 --> 17:35.280
No one has ever experienced such glorious joy.

17:35.340 --> 17:42.427
As Jesus says in John 17, verse 5, Father, glorify me with the glory I had before the world began.

17:42.467 --> 17:45.010
He is chosen and precious.

17:45.154 --> 17:45.775
to the Father.

17:46.216 --> 17:48.018
The Father treasures Him.

17:48.139 --> 17:53.026
Now, what did it cost the Father to lay that cornerstone in?

17:53.066 --> 18:00.878
The Bible tells us that He turned His back on His Son to pay the penalty for our sins.

18:02.781 --> 18:06.827
Now, if the Son was in the bosom of the Father, they were wrapped up in one of their souls.

18:06.847 --> 18:08.530
They loved each other like that.

18:08.642 --> 18:14.668
As John Flavell, that Puritan preacher I was just quoting from, as he says, no child was ever so one with its mother.

18:15.168 --> 18:16.950
No husband ever so one with his wife.

18:17.571 --> 18:21.634
No soul ever so one with its body as Jesus was with the father.

18:23.556 --> 18:26.940
And we're told that the father turned his back on his son.

18:27.000 --> 18:32.004
When his son was on the cross, Jesus says, my God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?

18:32.565 --> 18:33.426
And he was forsaken.

18:34.387 --> 18:37.810
And God the father turned his back and let his son be ripped to shreds.

18:38.402 --> 18:43.671
You know, I have only had my children a few years, not for eternity.

18:44.112 --> 18:48.279
And I have only held their bodies against my bosom, not their souls.

18:49.301 --> 18:53.028
And I love my children sometimes, but not always.

18:54.711 --> 19:03.506
But the Father and the Son were so infinitely intimate with each other, I can't imagine

19:03.810 --> 19:09.797
doing what the Father did to my children, and yet the Father did what He did to His Son for you.

19:09.817 --> 19:12.540
Do you see how precious the cornerstone is?

19:13.661 --> 19:16.424
Do you see what it costs God to lay the cornerstone?

19:17.765 --> 19:21.269
But that preciousness passes on to us.

19:22.270 --> 19:32.722
Jesus Christ actually has the audacity to say, in John chapter 17, when He's praying to the Father, He says, Father, I will that they be also where I am.

19:33.378 --> 19:39.784
And in verse 23, he says, let the world know that you have loved them even as you have loved me.

19:42.347 --> 19:48.673
Even as you have loved me, when you put your trust in him, when you build your life on him, what happens?

19:48.814 --> 19:50.475
Well, somebody says your sins get forgiven.

19:50.495 --> 19:51.056
Well, that's true.

19:51.476 --> 19:53.698
Well, somebody says, don't you get the Holy Spirit into your life?

19:53.758 --> 19:54.419
Yes, that's true.

19:55.160 --> 19:56.902
Well, somebody says, you're born again.

19:56.962 --> 20:01.266
Yes, we've been through all that these last few weeks, but I want you to see that this is higher than all of that.

20:02.242 --> 20:08.109
Because literally it says, because He is precious to the Father, you are acceptable.

20:08.610 --> 20:13.456
Literally, by the way, in verse 7 it says, to you who believe is the honor.

20:13.496 --> 20:25.330
The Bible says, Jesus says, the Father, when you believe in Jesus, the Father, loves you even as He loves His Son, can you imagine

20:25.698 --> 20:27.341
the reunion of the son and the father.

20:27.381 --> 20:31.149
Can you imagine the reunion after Jesus died and was raised and he goes back to the father?

20:31.510 --> 20:32.952
Can you imagine how they embraced?

20:32.993 --> 20:34.476
Can you imagine how they saw each other?

20:34.997 --> 20:37.862
The Bible says God loves you just the way he loves his son.

20:37.922 --> 20:45.037
Now a Christian boots off of that every day in all of their thoughts.

20:46.119 --> 20:47.762
That is the cornerstone.

20:48.034 --> 20:50.919
All of the lines of your life can be projected off of that.

20:51.099 --> 20:51.580
Don't you see?

20:51.900 --> 20:56.768
When you get criticized and you feel defensive, you say, wait a minute, all the charges have been dropped.

20:56.788 --> 20:59.012
He loves me even as he loves the sun.

20:59.052 --> 21:02.778
I'm as precious to him as the cornerstone.

21:02.798 --> 21:05.202
It's passed on to me.

21:05.242 --> 21:10.451
The integrity of the cornerstone, the preciousness of the cornerstone, the lines of the cornerstone.

21:10.751 --> 21:14.738
When you feel self-pity, you say, what in the world am I thinking of?

21:14.914 --> 21:16.356
Look what he went through for me.

21:16.916 --> 21:29.311
A Christian boots off of the fact that you are built into the cornerstone, that you now are offering acceptable sacrifices to you who believe is the honor.

21:30.052 --> 21:30.953
Do you understand that?

21:31.373 --> 21:32.335
Do you boot off of that?

21:33.356 --> 21:34.918
Do you see that he is your federal head?

21:34.938 --> 21:36.519
That means you're in federation with him.

21:37.080 --> 21:42.066
That what he is you are, he is the beloved son

21:42.434 --> 21:43.515
You're the beloved child.

21:43.875 --> 21:45.037
God is well pleased with him.

21:45.477 --> 21:46.538
God is well pleased with you.

21:47.019 --> 21:48.600
He is the apple of the Father's Eye.

21:48.900 --> 21:50.282
You are the apple of the Father's Eye.

21:50.322 --> 21:50.522
Why?

21:50.762 --> 21:51.863
Because he's the cornerstone.

21:51.883 --> 21:52.504
You're built in.

21:52.544 --> 21:58.490
There's many, many ways that the metaphors that the Bible uses to get across this whole idea, and this is one of them.

21:59.230 --> 22:00.171
Can you rest in that?

22:00.292 --> 22:01.453
Can you rejoice in that?

22:02.294 --> 22:04.255
Can you draw from this like a well?

22:04.616 --> 22:10.962
Look, last of all, even as you have loved me, lastly,

22:12.162 --> 22:13.504
Jesus has to be the love of your life.

22:15.647 --> 22:21.336
Verse seven, now to you who believe he is precious.

22:23.158 --> 22:30.009
My favorite story that illustrates that, I don't even remember where I got it, but I got years ago from some old sermon I read somewhere.

22:31.030 --> 22:33.814
I guess it was a Charles Spurgeon, the Baptist preacher from London.

22:34.916 --> 22:38.701
Spurgeon was preaching on this passage, now to you who believe he is precious.

22:39.543 --> 22:41.746
And he says, what happens is,

22:42.690 --> 22:55.843
When you understand that you're in federation with him, when you understand he's your cornerstone and what has passed to you because you're part of the corner, because you're built into the cornerstone, when you realize that, you become ravished with him.

22:57.624 --> 23:01.168
You know, as John Duns said, I will never be chased except you ravish me.

23:01.408 --> 23:03.650
What does it mean to be ravished with Jesus?

23:04.411 --> 23:11.858
It means to think about the things we're talking about until the preciouses of Jesus dawns on you.

23:12.066 --> 23:13.808
And Spurgeon tells the story this way.

23:14.890 --> 23:16.632
It's a pretty simple story.

23:16.732 --> 23:25.223
And he says, imagine that you were sick and dying, and I had a medicine that could cure you.

23:25.263 --> 23:29.068
And if I came to you and I said, I've got the medicine, I know the man who makes it.

23:29.448 --> 23:30.750
He would say, great, give it to me.

23:30.890 --> 23:34.034
And if I said, well, but it's going to be very, very, very expensive.

23:34.530 --> 23:36.954
It's going to cost a tremendous amount of money.

23:36.994 --> 23:38.376
You'd say, give it to me anyway.

23:38.797 --> 23:50.135
So, well, you know, if you're going to buy this medicine, you're going to have to actually sell all of your, you're going to have to sell your house and probably live in something, just a small little shack, shack someplace.

23:50.356 --> 23:51.858
That's all right, you say.

23:52.002 --> 23:52.603
I'll do it.

23:52.863 --> 23:56.327
Well, you're going to have to sell many of your possessions.

23:56.347 --> 23:57.568
You're going to have to hock your car.

23:57.588 --> 24:01.432
You're going to be living in absolute poverty if you're going to get this medicine.

24:01.472 --> 24:09.561
And you probably would say, this is how the illustration went, you'd probably say, what good is my car if I don't have that medicine?

24:10.382 --> 24:12.164
What good is my house if I don't have that medicine?

24:12.585 --> 24:14.727
What good is a vacation if I don't have that medicine?

24:15.388 --> 24:21.074
All these things that look so wonderful to me now become expendable

24:21.666 --> 24:24.552
in light of the preciousness of that medicine.

24:25.955 --> 24:27.358
Now here's how you can tell you're a Christian.

24:27.398 --> 24:33.451
Until you who believe he is precious, you know why Christians get generous with their money?

24:33.892 --> 24:40.466
You know why Christians no longer mind if people come into their homes and you know, tramp around and maybe mess up the rug?

24:41.090 --> 24:43.554
Do you know why people don't mind being imposed on anymore?

24:43.574 --> 24:47.059
Do you know why people, when they become Christians, aren't as selfish as they used to be?

24:47.679 --> 24:51.865
Do you know why people, when people who are Christians, when you become a Christian, your priorities are skewered.

24:51.885 --> 24:53.948
And other people think you have gone off your rocker.

24:54.850 --> 24:55.410
Do you know why?

24:55.430 --> 24:58.335
Because unto you who believe he's precious.

24:58.975 --> 25:06.386
And when one thing is so precious, everything else that used to look important becomes eternally and utterly expendable to you.

25:07.074 --> 25:08.215
Nothing else matters.

25:08.296 --> 25:09.397
Nothing else matters but Him.

25:09.437 --> 25:10.719
You're free.

25:10.779 --> 25:12.481
Nothing has you by the throat.

25:12.841 --> 25:14.764
Nothing you're scared to death to lose.

25:15.184 --> 25:16.326
Nothing you're running scared.

25:16.366 --> 25:20.511
Your franticness is gone because you're ravished with the beauty of Jesus.

25:20.952 --> 25:25.497
If Jesus becomes the love of your life, you can say goodbye to being afraid of anything else.

25:26.499 --> 25:31.825
If Jesus becomes the love of your life, there's a freedom unto you who believe he is precious.

25:32.246 --> 25:34.028
Unfortunately, there's a warning that goes with it.

25:34.449 --> 25:35.570
You know what the warning is?

25:37.474 --> 25:40.628
It says, the stone that the builders rejected has become the capstone.

25:40.648 --> 25:44.023
A stone that causes men to stumble and a rock that makes them fall.

25:44.686 --> 25:45.650
If you...

25:46.274 --> 25:47.696
Reject the cornerstone.

25:47.996 --> 25:53.081
This cornerstone is so big that it will be a tremendous hindrance for you finishing the house.

25:53.582 --> 25:57.106
What if you bring the cornerstone after you spend all this time and you reject the cornerstone?

25:57.126 --> 26:00.289
Well, you're going to bankrupt yourself because you spent so much money on it.

26:00.850 --> 26:04.794
And you're also going to be constantly stubbing your toe on it because it's the biggest stone there.

26:04.895 --> 26:07.938
And here you've rejected it and you're trying to build, that's the image.

26:07.998 --> 26:15.346
And what it means is if you are an accident, if there is no God, and you're just an accident,

26:15.906 --> 26:19.191
Then life is meaningless, and even love is an illusion.

26:19.211 --> 26:23.637
All that love is is just the way that molecules under your cranium happen to be vibrating at the time.

26:25.639 --> 26:32.168
But if he exists, if there is a creator, how can you avoid something that big?

26:33.290 --> 26:34.151
You won't be able to.

26:34.191 --> 26:34.572
Don't you see?

26:34.592 --> 26:35.213
That's the idea.

26:35.553 --> 26:39.058
The stone that the bill is rejected has become a stumbling stone.

26:41.186 --> 26:45.352
If there's no Jesus, if there is no God, if you're an accident, life is meaningless.

26:45.412 --> 26:45.972
Don't you see?

26:45.992 --> 27:10.866
On the other hand, if there is one, you've got to come to Him, or else you'll be stumbling over Him all of your life and maybe eternally come to Him to that living stone, rejected by men, but chosen by God and precious to Him, for it is written, He who trusts in Him will never be put to shame.

27:11.298 --> 27:11.799
Let's pray.

27:12.460 --> 27:14.803
Father, as we come to the table, we're going to come to You.

27:14.864 --> 27:29.246
We're coming to You and we're seeking to build ourselves into You, to have the lines of our lives and the dimensions of our lives be controlled by the lines and the dimensions of the being and the person and the work of our precious Savior, Jesus Christ.

27:29.867 --> 27:36.978
Would You help us all as we come to the Lord's table to more purely and thoroughly

27:37.282 --> 27:45.511
be built in every stone, every part of our lives against and into and around and upon the chief cornerstone.

27:45.551 --> 27:46.772
We don't want to stumble over him.

27:47.273 --> 27:49.035
We want our lives to be built upon him.

27:49.495 --> 27:50.877
We thank you that he's precious to you.

27:50.917 --> 27:52.138
He's precious to us.

27:53.039 --> 27:56.303
And because he's precious to you, we are precious to you too.

27:57.244 --> 28:01.148
Help us to rejoice in that tonight and draw our power from that.

28:01.188 --> 28:03.090
We pray in Jesus' name, amen.

28:07.970 --> 28:09.632
Thanks for listening to today's teaching.

28:10.193 --> 28:16.061
It's our prayer that you were encouraged by it and that it helps you apply the gospel to your life and share it with others.

28:16.662 --> 28:20.927
For more helpful resources from Tim Keller, visit gospelandlife.com.

28:20.947 --> 28:24.012
There, you can subscribe to The Life in the Gospel Quarterly Journal.

28:24.492 --> 28:30.220
When you do, you will also receive free articles, sermons, devotionals, and other great gospel-centered resources.

28:30.700 --> 28:33.164
Again, it's all at gospelandlife.com.

28:33.584 --> 28:37.810
You can also stay connected with us on Facebook, Instagram, YouTube, and X.

28:38.690 --> 28:40.494
Today's sermon was recorded in 1993.

28:40.694 --> 28:51.218
